data.meta_description: Daughter-in-law of Christian IX - Louise Josephine Eugenie of Sweden (1851 â€“ 1926) was Queen of Denmark as the spouse of King Frederick VIII of Denmark. She was the only daughter of King Charles XV of Sweden & Louise of the Netherlands. Her father once lovingly said about her: "She's an ugly devil, but she's funny!" Louise did not have a good relationship with her husband's family, especially not with her mother-in-law & her sisters-in-law & she received no support from her spouse.
